cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.CC 

This paper is about voting protocols and their complexity in terms of manipulation. The most relevant sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), which deals with the intersection of computer science and game theory, including voting theory. The paper also discusses the computational complexity of manipulating the protocols, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and tweaking existing protocols, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the complexity classes of the protocols, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
